Copilot is my ghostwriter — not for ideas, but for polish. It has streamlined my writing workflow to the point where what once took an hour now takes minutes. I draft, Copilot tightens. Grammar, structure, CFO‑tone — done.

Here’s what I don’t do: I don’t let Copilot generate the concepts, arguments, or frameworks. I’m not asking it for a write‑up on the 𝐟𝐫𝐚𝐮𝐝 𝐭𝐫𝐢𝐚𝐧𝐠𝐥𝐞 or a summary of working capital. I write the full piece myself, then ask Copilot to refine.

Most posts take two iterations. Occasionally I redraft a section. Other times I cut or expand. Then I finalize the tone, cadence, and clarity for posting.

Copilot accelerates the mechanics. The thinking still belongs to me.
